    slug: "masnoon-namaz-e-janaza-flax",
    description: `Masnoon Namaz e Janaza is a specialised Urdu-language book that focuses exclusively on the Islamic funeral prayer (Salat al-Janazah), providing a comprehensive and authoritative guide to performing this important communal obligation in accordance with the authentic Sunnah. This edition is produced with a flax-based cover material that gives the book a distinctive natural texture and appearance while ensuring durability for regular handling. The book addresses one of the most frequently needed yet often poorly understood acts of worship in Islam, as many Muslims may not encounter the funeral prayer frequently enough to memorise its procedure, yet it is a communal obligation (fard kifayah) that must be performed whenever a Muslim passes away. The text begins by explaining the significance and virtues of the funeral prayer in Islam, drawing upon relevant Quranic verses and hadith narrations that highlight the importance of accompanying the deceased to the graveyard and praying over them. The book then provides a thorough, step-by-step guide to performing the funeral prayer, covering the intention (niyyah), the four takbeers and what is recited after each one, the specific supplications for the deceased (including different du'as for adults, children, and males versus females), and the concluding salam. Each element is explained with reference to the relevant hadith narrations and the positions of the major schools of Islamic jurisprudence, allowing readers to understand the evidential basis for the procedures described. The book also covers important related topics such as the conditions for the validity of the funeral prayer, the rules regarding who is obligated to pray, the rulings on offering the funeral prayer in absentia (Salat al-Gha'ib), and the specific situations in which the funeral prayer may be omitted. Practical guidance is provided on arranging the funeral prayer, including the positioning of the imam, the congregation, and the deceased. The book addresses common mistakes and misunderstandings that people have about the funeral prayer, correcting them with clear evidence and scholarly consensus. A dedicated section covers the etiquette of visiting the graveyard and the supplications to recite for the deceased after burial. Written in clear and concise Urdu, this flax-bound edition is a practical reference that every mosque, Islamic centre, and Muslim household should keep readily accessible for the inevitable occasions when it is needed.`,
    metaDescription: "Masnoon Namaz e Janaza is a flax-bound Urdu guide to Islamic funeral prayer covering step-by-step procedure, supplications, and related rulings."
