    slug: "master-prayer-cap-made-in-bangladesh-56cm",
    description: `Master Prayer Cap Made in Bangladesh (56cm) is a high-quality, traditionally crafted Muslim prayer cap (topi) manufactured in Bangladesh using time-honoured techniques that have made Bangladeshi prayer caps renowned across the Muslim world. This cap is designed with a generous 56-centimetre circumference, making it suitable for most adult head sizes and providing a comfortable, secure fit that stays in place throughout the prayer. The prayer cap is an important part of the Muslim male's attire during Salah, as it follows the practice of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) who would often cover his head during prayer. This particular cap is crocheted or knitted using premium quality cotton yarn that is both breathable and durable, ensuring comfort during extended prayer sessions, recitation of the Quran, and daily wear. The open-work crochet design allows air circulation, which is especially beneficial in warmer climates and during the physically demanding movements of the prayer, particularly when performing multiple units or during Tarawih prayers in Ramadan. The 56cm size has been carefully calibrated to accommodate a wide range of head sizes without being too tight or too loose, providing a snug yet comfortable fit that does not shift or slip during the various positions of prayer, from standing and bowing to prostration and sitting. The craftsmanship reflects the skilled tradition of Bangladeshi textile workers who have been producing prayer caps for generations, with tight and even stitching that ensures the cap maintains its shape and durability through regular use and repeated washing. The cap is lightweight, making it easy to fold and carry in a pocket or bag when travelling to the mosque or on journeys. It is also easy to wash and maintain, retaining its shape and quality even after multiple wash cycles. This prayer cap is suitable for daily use in the five daily prayers, for wearing during Quran recitation and dhikr sessions, for attending Friday prayers and Eid gatherings, and for any occasion where a Muslim man wishes to maintain the dignified appearance that covering the head provides. The clean white or natural colour options make this cap versatile enough to complement any style of traditional or modern Islamic dress.`,
    metaDescription: "Master Prayer Cap 56cm from Bangladesh is a premium cotton crochet topi offering breathable comfort and secure fit for daily Salah."
